article.headline: Hawaii 89, San Francisco 85
article.story: HONOLULU (AP) -- Three Hawaii players scored more than 20 points to lead the Rainbow Warriors to an 89-85 win over San Francisco in the opening round of the Rainbow Classic Wednesday night. Matt Lojeski scored a team-high 24 points, Bobby Nash added 21 and Ahmet Gueye had 20 for Hawaii (6-4). Alan Wiggins led the Dons (4-8) with 24 points and Surratt added 22. With Hawaii up by three, Lojeski made a layup with 22 seconds remaining and Gueye blocked Armondo Surratts' shot on the following possession to secure the victory for the Rainbow Warriors. Hawaii led by as much as 16 in the second half, but San Francisco scored seven consecutive points in less than a minute to pull to within seven, 77-70, with 3:54 remaining. The Dons closed the gap to three, 84-81, with 1:36 remaining. The Rainbow Warriors led 41-30 at halftime. Hawaii advances to face Nebraska in semifinals of the Rainbow Classic Friday night.
